article.description: Lonnie Jackson scored 19 points and Chandler Hutchinson added 17 points and seven rebounds to help lead Boise State to a 100-36 win over NAIA Willamette on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Boise State tramples Willamette, 100-36
article.story: BOISE, Idaho -- Lonnie Jackson scored 19 points and Chandler Hutchinson added 17 points and seven rebounds to help lead Boise State to a 100-36 win over NAIA Willamette on Wednesday night. Paris Austin finished with 16 points and James Webb III had 13 points and a team-high 10 boards for the Broncos (4-4), who snapped a two-game losing streak to even their record. It was the third consecutive time Boise State has topped the century mark at home, the first such feat in the program. Boise State shot 56.1 percent from the field and had 20 assists. The Broncos had a 14-0 first half run and led 52-21 at the half. They opened the second half with a 16-6 stretch and pushed the lead to 50 on a Zach Haney jumper with 7:44 left. Nico Troplent scored 14 to lead Willamette.
